task.summary: Changed the main list data structure to a set in both the Python & Java coupon problem solutions to increase speed & efficiency.
Changed console output and also implemented a single Random object to forgo the creation of multiple Math.random objects.
Made iterative solutions start checking at the integer number of variants instead, and also refactored several other variable names.
Implemented a method for finding standard deviation of a given list.
Implemented a method for finding standard deviation of a given list.
Changed Java random number generator over to XorShift for speed increases. Also, created initial Scala directory for future work.
Removed C++ directory, added Scala directory, and finalized solution to the coupon problem in both Java and Python.
Renamed directories, edited the pseudo-code for the Java Coupon Problem solutions, and also began work on a 3-team round robin-style bracket generator.
Added preliminary Python script for solving the scheduling problem.
Added a means of finding undesirable team intersections.
Added Nicholas Kempf's Netlogo simulation and also fixed a bug in the Python bracketmaker.
Refactored some variables and also added to the Python solution for the Scheduling Problem.
Updated Variant Sampler to reset totals after each calculation.
